ing.\"},{\"type\":\"summary_text\",\"text\":\"**Examining test coverage issues**\\n\\nI'm starting to wonder if the pipeline only ran the previous placeholder tests. It seems that our test might not be under the correct target. I need to consider if we didn't compile or run the tests, which might be why there's no coverage reported. I wonder if JUnit is initializing the class during test discovery, but that doesn't seem to be the case, nor do static imports seem to be the issue. I'm concerned that the native image build is initializing `HttpMessageConverters` at build time by default.\"}]}"}, {"type": "toolCall", "id": "call_ElHGTiJbmejMmOdZq3AAPI8a|fc_04dbbb8c710fddbc016a0c511cb60481a295dfb2a0305274dd", "name": "bash", "arguments": {"command": "rg \"NativeImageSupport|isUnsupportedFeatureError|URLClassLoader|FilteredClassLoader\" tests/src -g '*.java' | head -80"}}], "api": "openai-responses", "provider": "OCA", "model": "gpt-5.5", "usage": {"input": 2304, "output": 1040, "cacheRead": 22016, "cacheWrite": 0, "totalTokens": 25360, "cost": {"input": 0, "output": 0, "cacheRead": 0, "cacheWrite": 0, "total": 0}}, "stopReason": "toolUse", "timestamp": 1779192075355, "responseId": "resp_04dbbb8c710fddbc016a0c510c02b881a2bb6c1215482abdee"}, "toolResults": [{"role": "toolResult", "toolCallId": "call_ElHGTiJbmejMmOdZq3AAPI8a|fc_04dbbb8c710fddbc016a0c511cb60481a295dfb2a0305274dd", "toolName": "bash", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "tests/src/org.apache.pulsar/pulsar-client-api/4.2.1/src/test/java/org_apache_pulsar/pulsar_client_api/ReflectionUtilsTest.java:import org.graalvm.internal.tck.NativeImageSupport;\ntests/src/org.apache.pulsar/pulsar-client-api/4.2.1/src/test/java/org_apache_pulsar/pulsar_client_api/ReflectionUtilsTest.java:        if (!NativeImageSupport.isUnsupportedFeatureError(error)) {\ntests/src/jdom/jdom/1.0/src/test/java/jdom/jdom/SAXBuilderTest.java:import org.graalvm.internal.tck.NativeImageSupport;\ntests/src/jdom/jdom/1.0/src/test/java/jdom/jdom/SA